This paper discusses the use of cognitive and cooperative techniques for improving the energy efficiency of cellular networks. It involves spectrum sensing, wireless access networks, and transmission optimization, which are all related to the field of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of information theory for optimizing transmission strategies (cs.IT), and the use of multimedia communication for supporting cellular communications (cs.MM). The paper also involves system-level optimization and control, which are related to the field of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses security and privacy issues related to cognitive networks, which are related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
